<taxonomicName id="357AA5C28E2B55F99C318F9150313653" authorityName="Lethierry" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Idiocerus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Idiocerus clypealis" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypealis">Idiocerus clypealis</taxonomicName>
Lethierry, 1889: 252-Matsumura 1912: 322 (Taiwan).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="448387EFC560DFCB3A11DD7926641C90" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<taxonomicName id="FD91480CD6A634023AE0C114AF8A386E" authorityName="Lethierry" authorityYear="1889" baseAuthorityName="Lethierry" baseAuthorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Idioscopus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Idioscopus clypealis" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypealis">Idioscopus clypealis</taxonomicName>
- 
<bibRefCitation id="7D66BAE3EE8BF2E9A96F25EDD5B8746D" author="Maldonado-Capriles, J" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="89 - 100" refId="B7" refString="Maldonado-Capriles, J, 1964. Studies on Idiocerinae leafhoppers: II. The Indian and Philippine species of Idiocerus and the genus Idioscopus (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 66: 89 - 100" title="Studies on Idiocerinae leafhoppers: II. The Indian and Philippine species of Idiocerus and the genus Idioscopus (Homoptera: Cicadellidae)." volume="66" year="1964">Maldonado Capriles 1964</bibRefCitation>
: 92-93, figs 6-9; 
<bibRefCitation id="0C1C946D20FEB2839E21C6F98E94659F" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3860.3.6" author="Khatri, I" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Taiwan Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" refId="B4" refString="Khatri, I, Webb, MD, 2014. Review of the idiocerine leafhoppers of Pakistan (Hemiptera, Cicadellidae) with a description of a new species. Zootaxa 3860(3): e280. https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3860.3.6" title="Review of the idiocerine leafhoppers of Pakistan (Hemiptera, Cicadellidae) with a description of a new species. Zootaxa 3860 (3): e 280." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3860.3.6" year="2014">Khatri and Webb 2014</bibRefCitation>
: 282-284, table 1, fig. 5.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B77D095ED8F5BA30C8C0BCE314BC2FCC" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<taxonomicName id="890DE78414F4998AAB775F972C5073F0" authorityName="Huang &amp; Maldonado-Capriles" authorityYear="1992" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Idioscopus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Idioscopus taiwanus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taiwanus">Idioscopus taiwanus</taxonomicName>
Huang &amp; Maldonado-Capriles, 1992: 7, fig. 3, syn. nov.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7B207B7669A99631095FE7ABAEF48E1A" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="3513D17B16FDC56D20A77C43172AE5CF" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="46CFBDF276136B47D9515613F9AF16D8" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
The above synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="E985F0A3B0183959D3782C1DCB0A3244" genus="I." lsidName="I. taiwanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" rank="species" species="taiwanus">
<emphasis id="809E9796286FFF5ADAEC4083B28A6123" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">I. taiwanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="C05E03B1B1EAAC7E0150A67215A016BD" genus="I." lsidName="I. clypealis" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" rank="species" species="clypealis">
<emphasis id="4366FB1149BDD30172C5E45F97602FBF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">I. clypealis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on the similarity of the published figures of both species and examination of some paratypes of 
<taxonomicName id="1213BB9FB4461BDECF3370A3280D3D86" genus="I." lsidName="I. taiwanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" rank="species" species="taiwanus">
<emphasis id="C1C9D13F4675F614BB906B80BB1E3F96" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">I. taiwanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below). It is surprising that 
<taxonomicName id="37412C055E1D20062316AE613DD45DB9" genus="I." lsidName="I. taiwanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" rank="species" species="taiwanus">
<emphasis id="8AA5E6112AA15DD195B2FF351A9CD06F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">I. taiwanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described as a new species and not recognized as the widespread 
<taxonomicName id="A93A4A656B85C3BC4D361E108B131E0D" genus="I." lsidName="I. clypealis" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" rank="species" species="clypealis">
<emphasis id="A215A21A0DFFF37B315AA7C7C798F2D8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">I. clypealis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as the latter species was well-known to Maldonado-Capriles and had been earlier figured by him (
<bibRefCitation id="1EB64BA328114C09FDE04538EBECD06F" author="Maldonado-Capriles, J" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="89 - 100" refId="B7" refString="Maldonado-Capriles, J, 1964. Studies on Idiocerinae leafhoppers: II. The Indian and Philippine species of Idiocerus and the genus Idioscopus (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 66: 89 - 100" title="Studies on Idiocerinae leafhoppers: II. The Indian and Philippine species of Idiocerus and the genus Idioscopus (Homoptera: Cicadellidae)." volume="66" year="1964">Maldonado-Capriles 1964</bibRefCitation>
). Also, the described colour of 
<taxonomicName id="8B537F62D9C5431202B5634D339514F9" genus="I." lsidName="I. taiwanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" rank="species" species="taiwanus">
<emphasis id="458D788A7201C6ECC1BCAEC0B3F95C68" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">I. taiwanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
more or less matches the 
<normalizedToken id="49699B431745D1E59208F1232C0E0C31" originalValue="“typical”">&quot;typical&quot;</normalizedToken>
colour form of 
<taxonomicName id="619A26EC9FA706B2CD675B4CB00D6B0B" genus="I." lsidName="I. clypealis" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" rank="species" species="clypealis">
<emphasis id="7A8143E135DC9E8D4B5F9B2BE5320261" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">I. clypealis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
figured by the same author and latter figured by 
<bibRefCitation id="DC9DD9D21074B190370689A80D5EE6D3" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3860.3.6" author="Khatri, I" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Taiwan Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" refId="B4" refString="Khatri, I, Webb, MD, 2014. Review of the idiocerine leafhoppers of Pakistan (Hemiptera, Cicadellidae) with a description of a new species. Zootaxa 3860(3): e280. https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3860.3.6" title="Review of the idiocerine leafhoppers of Pakistan (Hemiptera, Cicadellidae) with a description of a new species. Zootaxa 3860 (3): e 280." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3860.3.6" year="2014">Khatri and Webb (2014)</bibRefCitation>
from mainland Asia. A variation of this colour is seen in some specimens collected from mainland China which have more extensive brown marking medially on the face (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4CC4E1F445E1EA3D323C7B0A97692572" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Idioscopus clypealis A-C female (China) A lateral habitus female B, C face (male and female respectively) showing atypical marking of clypeus; photographs by Xue Qingquan D-G paratype male of I. taiwanus D dorsal habitus E lateral habitus F ventral habitus G labels H-K paratype female of I. taiwanus H dorsal habitus I lateral habitus J ventral habitus K labels; photographs by David Redei." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671695" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">4A-C</figureCitation>
), matching some Pacific material figured by 
<bibRefCitation id="42C30A3B0A0DF6FBA9B51E66B14F9ABA" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3860.3.6" author="Khatri, I" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Taiwan Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" refId="B4" refString="Khatri, I, Webb, MD, 2014. Review of the idiocerine leafhoppers of Pakistan (Hemiptera, Cicadellidae) with a description of a new species. Zootaxa 3860(3): e280. https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3860.3.6" title="Review of the idiocerine leafhoppers of Pakistan (Hemiptera, Cicadellidae) with a description of a new species. Zootaxa 3860 (3): e 280." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3860.3.6" year="2014">Khatri and Webb (2014)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
